  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Where can I get a large corpus of news articles with pictures?",
  "response": "There are several sources where you can find large corpora of news articles with pictures. Here are some options:\n\n1. **News APIs**: Many news organizations provide APIs that allow you to access their articles along with images. Some popular ones include:\n   - **Google News API**: Aggregates news articles from various sources.\n   - **NewsAPI.org**: Provides access to many news articles and images from various publishers.\n   - **Bing News Search API**: Offers access to news articles and associated images.\n\n2. **Web Scraping**: If you have the technical expertise, you can scrape websites for news articles and images. Popular news websites include:\n   - CNN\n   - BBC\n   - Reuters\n   - The New York Times\n   - The Guardian\n   Be sure to check their terms of service concerning web scraping.\n\n3. **Online Datasets**: Some universities or data repositories offer datasets that include news articles and images, such as:\n   - The Kaggle Datasets: Search for news articles datasets.\n   - The Reuters News Dataset: Contains a large collection of news articles.\n   - The Common Crawl dataset: A large archive of web pages including news articles.\n\n4. **Image Search Engines**: For pictures, you can use image repositories or stock photo sites that might permit use in conjunction with articles, though licensing can vary.\n   - Unsplash\n   - Pexels\n   - Pixabay\n\n5. **Public Domain and Creative Commons Sites**: Resources like Wikimedia Commons or sites with open licenses may provide access to news-related images that can be freely used alongside articles.\n\n6. **Institutional Access**: If you are affiliated with an academic institution, check if they have access through library subscriptions to news databases (like ProQuest or Factiva) which might also provide images along with articles.\n\nMake sure to comply with copyright laws and the terms of service of the platforms you use. Always cite sources and give proper credit for images where necessary.",
